cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.HC 

The paper describes the development of a neural network decision tree for classification of EEG data. This involves the use of machine learning techniques such as linear tests and a new training algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of neural networks and decision trees suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The use of EEG data and feature extraction techniques suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) may also be relevant. Finally, the application of the developed algorithm to classify EEG recordings suggests that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) may also be relevant.
